==English==

===Alternative spellings===
knopkierie.

===Etymology===
A [[portmanteau]] word from Afrikaans ''Knop'' meaning knob + Khoi-San ''kirri'' or ''keeri'' meaning stick.

===Noun===
'''knobkierie'''

# (South African) A fighting stick usually with a knob on the end.
# A [[bludgeon]]. 

===Related Terms===
* Kierie
*Austraian: nulla-nulla.
*Canadian: casse-tetê.

===Reference===
Jean Bradford. A dictionary of South African English. Oxford 1978.

